//npm init is a command used to create a new Node.js project.

//it create package.json file,which store

->your project details
->Installed npm packages or project dependencies(express,mongoose)
-> Scripts to run your project:instead of typing long terminal commands, you can put them inside "scripts" and run them easily.




//When you run:npm init

It will ask questions like:

project name

version

description

entry point (e.g., index.js)

author

license

After that, it creates:package.json